"\n| --- | --- |\n| What is organizational behavior? | Organizational behavior is an academic discipline focused on understanding and managing people at work. |\n| What is the goal of organizational behavior? | The goal of organizational behavior is to overcome the pitfalls of relying on common sense by relying on a systematic science-based approach. |\n| What are the three levels of organizational behavior? | The three levels of organizational behavior are individual, group/team, and organization. |\n| What is the value of organizational behavior to my job and career? | The value of organizational behavior to my job and career lies in its ability to help me develop soft skills that are highly valued by employers. These soft skills include personal attributes such as teamwork and leadership, as well as interpersonal skills such as active listening and effective communication. |"